On 2001-06-14 02:02, Flaim wrote:
Myzzrim
Registered User
(5/11/01 4:12:35 am)
Reply  Levelling quickly from 16 to 24
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Hi all,

Thought I might tip you on my knowledge of fast levelling those levels. Now as I did this a few months ago the camps might be crowded now. They werent then.

1) Head to Lake Rathe (south of South K). Once there, head to the far South-west corner. There's some kind of water corridor leading to a small piece of grass with a hut, and a guy named Jonah. He'll aggro you on sight. Just kick his butt fast and camp him for 2-3 levels. He's on 5 minutes spawn time, drops crappy loot (waterskins most of the time), but yields TREMENDOUS xp at these levels. You can practically kill him as soon as he spawns, as you have enough time to med before he spawns again. Dont forget to spikebomb yourself for the melee.

2) On hitting 20 (or 19 if high wis), you may consider Aviak guards. Now there are some camps scattered around this zone, but the best spot I found were two aviaks in a hut very near Jonah. Leaving Jonah, you head west and north (in water), and the hut is the first one on your left. Since there are two aviaks, you need to break the spawns. You do that by harmoing them (just climb on the side cliff to get in range), then kick'em. This camp was so safe I stayed in treeform the whole time (HP regen easyer) and just killed one after the other with NOONE bothering me and absolutely no risk.

3) The hermit in South K. This i hear is a highly camped spot nowadays. You should consider kicking his butt around 24. Yields very good xp and very good loot (FS weapons on an uncommon basis).

Now I am a halfling, so xp is rumored easyer for us. But doing this (especially Jonah and the aviaks) I was making one orange bubble XP every 35 minutes. From 16 to 24. Cheers 8^)

PS: As a general rule, at those levels, when meleing was still possible, I would remain in treeform for hp regen and spikebomb myself (Shield of **, **armor). And never worry about healing myself. 
 
